This paper focuses on Compressive Sensing (CS) reconstruction of natural images using optimization-inspired neural networks. The paper discusses the limitations of existing networks and proposes a new network called MC-ISTA-Net that addresses these limitations. Given that the paper deals with image reconstruction, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new neural network architecture, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of iterative algorithms and optimization techniques, which could place it in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with multi-channel feature maps and channel attention, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
